# Git commands

When the answer involves version control (commit, push, branch, deploy from Git, undo, sync, etc.), **always include the recommended `git` commands** in copy-pasteable form (full commands, PowerShell-friendly when the user is on Windows).

Do not only describe steps in prose—pair each workflow with the exact commands to run.

**Typical deploy for this repo (after `npm run build`), if `main` is the default branch:**

```powershell
cd c:\Users\Johnd\MotionCalc
git status
git add -A
git commit -m "Describe your change"
git push origin main
```

Use `master` instead of `main` if that is the project’s default branch.
